            <h1>Understanding Your Test Results</h1>
                <p>
                    Your performance on a test is evaluated against an esta=
blished standard. Total test scores are based on all sections of a test and=
 are reported on a scale with a range of 100 to 300. Each test has its own =
passing score set by the Utah State Board of Education (<a href=3D"https://=
www.ut.nesinc.com/PageView.aspx?f=3DGEN_Tests.html">select your test</a> to=
 see passing score). A total test scaled score equal to or higher than the =
passing score is required to pass the test.=20
                </p>
			=09
				<p>
<b>Scoring open responses.</b> Information about the scoring of open respon=
ses, including performance characteristics and the score scale, is availabl=
e in the <a href=3D"https://www.ut.nesinc.com/PageView.aspx?f=3DHTML_FRAG/G=
ENRB_PrepStudyGuide.html" target=3D"_blank">open-response section of the st=
udy guide.</a>
</p>
			=09
				<h2>Scoring Series FLEX</h2>

				<p>
					Series FLEX submissions are scored holistically by two or more indepen=
dent scorers. Scorers judge the overall effectiveness of each submission us=
ing a performance score scale and a set of performance characteristics. Ref=
er to the Study Guide in the Prepare section of the National Evaluation Ser=
ies=E2=84=A2 program website for more information. Passing status is based =
on your score for the Series FLEX submission.
				</p>

                <h2>How to Read Your Score Report</h2>

                <p>
                    Examinees who take a National Evaluation Series=E2=84=
=A2 test to meet Utah State Department of Education certification requireme=
nts will receive a National Evaluation Series score report with diagnostic =
information that indicates whether the examinee has met the Utah requiremen=
ts for that test.=20
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li class=3D"pdf"><a href=3D"https://www.ut.nesinc.com/=
Content/Docs/FOR_UT_ScoreReportBacker_890.pdf">National Evaluation Series=
=E2=84=A2 Score Report Explanation </a></li>
					<li class=3D"pdf"><a href=3D"https://www.ut.nesinc.com/Content/Docs/FL=
EX_ScoreReportBacker.pdf">National Evaluation Series FLEX Score Report Expl=
anation</a></li>
                </ul>


